cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper focuses on data mining techniques applied to social interaction networks, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of predictive algorithms (cs.SD) and community detection (cs.IR) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data mining for improving user experience (cs.HC) and the analysis of real-world face-to-face contact networks, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) for modeling human behavior.
